parameters: \n<Detective>I have to chase after those girls...
\n<Detective>I have to chase after those girls...
\n<???>...I heard you have something to do with Marilyn.

\n<???>A...Aria-chan...Don't call Komari in a weird
way...

\n<???>...Well then, I've shown you the way... The rest
is up to you two.

\n<Detective>Ah... well, like I heard earlier, it's about
that... Ichiru girl...

\n<???>W-What are you planning to do to Ichiru-chan!?
D-Don't tell me... s-something lewd...

\n<Detective>Wait a minute, as a police officer, I need to talk
to you for a moment...

\n<???>P-Police!? You're not planning to arrest Ichiru-
chan, are you!?

\n<Detective>No, no, it's not that... I want to talk to you
about the incident for a moment...

\n<???>Incident!? Suspect!?... Could it be a false
accusation...!? H...How terrible... Ichiru-chan
hasn't done anything...

\n<Detective>No, please calm down and listen to what I have to
say...

\n<???>Uwaaaah! Ichiru-chaaaan! Scary adults... corrupt
police officers are threatening meee!

\n<Detective>...What speed... but now is not the time to be
impressed. For now, I need to chase after them.

\n<???>Who the hell are you? The bastard who bullied my
Komari.
\n<???>...Huh? Is that so? You're quick, old man.

\n<???>N-No, it's not like that, Ichiru-chan... This
person came to protect you, Ichiru-chan...

\n<Detective>(Ichiru...!? So, it must be this child after
all...)

\n<???>Detective...? I have nothing to do with that old
bastard anymore. I have no connection with the
gang either.

\n<Detective>No, that's not it. It's not that I want to ask
about that...

\n<Detective>I'm investigating the \c[2]phenomenon of people
going insane\c[0] that's happening in Sakuhai
City, and the \c[2]suspects\c[0] who are suspected
to be involved.

\n<???>...Was the Kureha Group involved in the
development project in Sakuhai City?
\n<Detective>Ah, if you happen to know anything about that...

\n<???>I don't know. But it's the kind of thing that
scumbags who prioritize money over honor would do.
They probably did exactly what I expected.
\n<???>I see, so you're trying to stop Onee-san, huh?

\n<Detective>...! Then, if she... isn't stopped, the city will
be overrun with lunatics! As a detective...

\n<???>Investigating the phenomenon of people going
insane is your job. I have no intention of
stopping that.

\n<???>But we owe a debt of gratitude to Onee-san. We
can't just stay silent when there's a guy right in
front of us trying to cause harm. Ai! Komari!
\n<???>...Hmm. In that case, I'll get ready.

\n<???>Pya! Ugh... Don't scream out of nowhere...
Alright, I'll go let everyone know.

\n<Detective>Wait! I'm not planning on resorting to violent
measures! I just need to find a way to stop this
phenomenon...!

\n<???>I couldn't care less. I never said what Onee-san
is doing is a good thing.

\n<???>We're just repaying the debt of gratitude to Onee-
san. She saved us, who had nowhere else to go,
from those damn adults.

\n<???>If you want to reach Onee-san, you'll have to get
past us first. If you can, that is.

\n<Detective>...Damn it!...Where am I...an abandoned building?
Anyway, I have no choice but to keep chasing.
